home overview faq projects publications about us chronus chronus over the past decade the number size and complexity of databases for biomedical research have grown dramatically as a result the opportunities for data driven inquiry have expanded enormously and led to new challenges in informatics research the detection of temporal trends and temporal patterns in data is central to much of this research although such temporal queries are common indeed central in these analyses the biomedical field has no standard means for making them chronus is a tool that attempts to address this problem chronus is a database mediator that extends the sql query language and the standard relational model to support temporal queries on relational databases it provides an expressive sql based temporal query langauge that allows users to easily write complex temporal queries
